var program = [{"id":"1","title":"AttrAction","date":"2019-01-17","time":"12:00","mins":"60","desc":"The reactive interplay between the magnets in AttrAction is what gives this game its spark! Players must flick their \"shooter\" magnet into the playing area to attract and collect other magnets. Of course, it's not quite that easy since the magnets repel as easily as they attract! Strategies unfold and develop in reaction to the patterns on the table.","loc":["Greenfield"]},{"id":"2","title":"Celeste","date":"2019-01-17","time":"12:00","mins":"60","desc":"you board an aircraft with a team of adventurers to perform many trips through the cities of Celestia and recover their wonderful treasures. Your journey will not be safe, but you will attempt to be the richest adventurer by collecting the most precious treasures!","loc":["Greenfield"]},{"id":"3","title":"Roll for the Galaxy","date":"2019-01-17","time":"12:00","mins":"60","desc":"Build a space empire direct your populace to develop new technologies, settle worlds, and ship goods. The player who best manages his workers and builds the most prosperous empire wins!","loc":["Greenfield"]},{"id":"4","title":"The Business of Episodic Storytelling","date":"2019-01-17","time":"13:00","mins":"60","desc":"Serialized fiction has experienced a renaissance in the age of the internet. Our panelists discuss the business side of episodic storytelling-- What are the trade-offs between self-publishing and going with a publisher like Serial Box? If going through a publisher, how do you pitch serialized projects? If self-publishing, which platform is best for your work and audience?","loc":["Erie"],"people":[{"name":"Michael R. Underwood","id":"99"},{"name":"Mackenzie Flohr","id":"87"},{"name":"E.D.E. (Emily) Bell","id":"47"},{"name":"Christian Klaver","id":"27"}]},{"id":"5","title":"Alien Artifacts","date":"2019-01-17","time":"13:00","mins":"60","desc":"Build powerful ships, develop new technologies, and explore distant planets for anything (or anyone) you can exploit. Fight the Ancients or each other. 2017 Golden Geek Best Card Game nominee.","loc":["Greenfield"]},{"id":"6","title":"Attraction","date":"2019-01-17","time":"13:00","mins":"60","desc":"The reactive interplay between the magnets in AttrAction is what gives this game its spark! Players must flick their \"shooter\" magnet into the playing area to attract and collect other magnets. Of course, it's not quite that easy since the magnets repel as easily as they attract! Strategies unfold and develop in reaction to the patterns on the table.","loc":["Greenfield"]},{"id":"7","title":"Networking for Genre Fiction Professionals","date":"2019-01-17","time":"13:00","mins":"60","desc":"Some people hate the idea of networking, feel it's \"shmoozing\" or disingenuous communication. But it's highly useful to building a creative career. Panelists will talk about how networking has helped their careers (or not) and how to do it right.","loc":["Ontario"],"people":[{"name":"Dyrk Ashton","id":"45"},{"name":"Ferrett Steinmetz","id":"52"},{"name":"Cherie Priest","id":"25"},{"name":"Dan Wells","id":"35"}]},{"id":"8","title":"An Author's Guide To Newsletters","date":"2019-01-17","time":"14:00","mins":"60","desc":"Keeping up with the shifting landscape of social media can me a tall order for busy writers. E-mail newsletters are a simple, effective way to let your most engaged fans know where to find you and your work. Our panelists have tips on how to set up and maintain an effective newsletter.","loc":["Erie"],"people":[{"name":"Lawrence M. Schoen","id":"84"},{"name":"Marissa Lingen","id":"89"},{"name":"Patrick S. Tomlinson","id":"109"},{"name":"Natalie Luhrs","id":"102"}]},{"id":"9","title":"Castle Panic","date":"2019-01-17","time":"14:00","mins":"60","desc":"he forest is filled with all sorts of monsters. They watched and waited as you built your castle and trained your soldiers, but now they've gathered their army and are marching out of the woods. Can you work with your friends to defend your castle against the horde, or will the monsters tear down your walls and destroy the precious castle towers? You will all win or lose together, but in the end only one player will be declared the Master Slayer!","loc":["Greenfield"]},{"id":"10","title":"Good to the Last Drop (4hrs)","date":"2019-01-17","time":"14:00","mins":"60","desc":"You stumble upon a city seemingly under siege by mutanoid forces empowered by strange arcane magics. Running low on morale and supplies you are asked by a desperate populace to save them by destroying the menace. Simple enough, or is there more to this story...","loc":["Greenfield"]},{"id":"11","title":"Death March to a Parallel World (3hrs)","date":"2019-01-17","time":"14:00","mins":"60","loc":["Henry Ford"]},{"id":"12","title":"Commas Are An Art, Not A Science (And Other Copyediting Notes)","date":"2019-01-17","time":"14:00","mins":"60","desc":"Come and hear the wit and wisdom of professional copy-editors, who wish to sing you the song of well-placed commas and how they can contribute to your storytelling.","loc":["Ontario"],"people":[{"name":"Stephanie Lorée","id":"122"},{"name":"Richard Shealy","id":"114"},{"name":"Vanessa Ricci-Thode","id":"129"},{"name":"Melissa Ann Singer","id":"93"},{"name":"Teresa Nielsen Hayden","id":"126"}]},{"id":"13","title":"Paint and Take (6hrs)","date":"2019-01-17","time":"15:00","mins":"60","loc":["Atrium"]},{"id":"14","title":"A Pro Writer's Guide To Consultants","date":"2019-01-17","time":"15:00","mins":"60","desc":"There are a wealth of consulting services available to professional writers these days, including paid editing, sensitivity reading, marketing and social media consulting, and career coaching. What can these consulting services offer to trad and indie authors? When are they a good investment, and how do you vet and choose providers?","loc":["Erie"],"people":[{"name":"Richard Shealy","id":"114"},{"name":"Dan Stout","id":"34"},{"name":"Michael R. Underwood","id":"99"},{"name":"Dan Wells","id":"35"}]},{"id":"15","title":"Dice Forge","date":"2019-01-17","time":"15:00","mins":"60","desc":"Dice Forge is a development game featuring innovative mechanics based on dice with removable faces. In this dice crafting game, players build their own dice to gain resources to purchase upgrades.","loc":["Greenfield"]},{"id":"16","title":"Rising Sun (3hrs)","date":"2019-01-17","time":"15:00","mins":"60","desc":"A game for up to 6 players about feudal era japan where players are controlling different clans attempting to become the next ruler of japan. This game focuses on negotiation over force of arms as having an ally can often swing the tide of war in your favor.","loc":["Greenfield"]},{"id":"17","title":"Project Management Software In Publishing","date":"2019-01-17","time":"15:00","mins":"60","desc":"Taking a title from manuscript (or idea) to the finished product requires more than an editor who polishes and enhances the story. Distributing the correct information to various channels can become cumbersome when relying on classic spreadsheet styles. Project management tools are plentiful in the market from custom software to free online organizers. How can strategies in project management help create a smoother product?","loc":["Ontario"],"people":[{"name":"Geralyn Lance","id":"53"},{"name":"LaShawn M. Wanak","id":"82"},{"name":"Chris Bell","id":"26"},{"name":"Natalie Luhrs","id":"102"}]},{"id":"18","title":"Cultivating a Fanbase as a Publisher","date":"2019-01-17","time":"16:00","mins":"60","desc":"Just as fans follow specific authors or magazines, with the proliferation of small presses, we're increasingly seeing publishing houses develop followings of their own. Apex Publishing, Subterranean Press, World Weaver Press, Small Beer Press and many others have distinct voices and aesthetics which distinguish them in the marketplace. Some, such as Ugly Duckling Presse and Restless Books, offer annual subscriptions to their catalogs. Are readers following publishers as they follow authors, and what are publishers doing to cultivate fan bases?","loc":["Erie"],"people":[{"name":"Pablo Defendini","id":"107"},{"name":"Yanni Kuznia","id":"130"},{"name":"Michael J. DeLuca","id":"97"},{"name":"Joe R. Lansdale","id":"64"}]},{"id":"19","title":"Paperback","date":"2019-01-17","time":"16:00","mins":"60","desc":"Word-building meets deck-building in the unique game Paperback. Players start with a deck of letter cards and wild cards. Each hand they form words, and purchase more powerful letters based on how well their word scored. Players buy wilds to gain victory points.","loc":["Greenfield"]},{"id":"20","title":"Running Productive Critique Groups","date":"2019-01-17","time":"16:00","mins":"60","desc":"Critique groups can be a huge source of support for writers. They can provide practical advice on the architecture and carpentry of our stories, camaraderie and social support from folks within our career cohort, and mutual accountability to actually get things done. Our panelists have advice on how to build and maintain productive crit groups.","loc":["Ontario"],"people":[{"name":"Jordan Kurella","id":"71"},{"name":"Tim Boerger","id":"127"},{"name":"Lucy A. Snyder","id":"86"},{"name":"Anthony W. Eichenlaub","id":"13"}]},{"id":"21","title":"Escapism, Coming Back, and Beyond","date":"2019-01-17","time":"17:00","mins":"60","desc":"Fans of SFF can get pretty prickly about their escapist pleasures. In the era of #metoo, #ownvoices and bot-fueled reactionary troll backlash, it's time to unpack that. What do we get by escaping the real world into fiction for a little while? How does it feel coming back? How else can fiction help us weather and overcome the hardships of the real world, and how can it hurt?","loc":["Allen Park"],"people":[{"name":"Eric Anderson","id":"49"},{"name":"Sandee Rodriguez","id":"115"},{"name":"Andrea Johnson","id":"8"},{"name":"Jessi Cole Jackson","id":"62"}]},{"id":"22","title":"Writing Tie-In Fiction","date":"2019-01-17","time":"15:00","mins":"60","desc":"Tie-in fiction can help writers expand their fanbase, put money in the bank, and occasionally even propel writers onto bestseller lists--but working in a world over which you have limited creative control comes with its own set of challenges. Panelists who've written tie-ins will talk about the differences between tie-in and original work, how to navigate in someone else's sandbox, and what they wish they'd known when they started.","loc":["Erie"],"people":[{"name":"James L. Sutter","id":"54"},{"name":"Mur Lafferty","id":"101"},{"name":"Nathan Rockwood","id":"103"},{"name":"Delilah Dawson","id":"40"}]},{"id":"23","title":"Sushi Go","date":"2019-01-17","time":"17:00","mins":"60","desc":"you are eating at a sushi restaurant and trying to grab the best combination of sushi dishes as they whiz by. Score points for collecting the most sushi rolls or making a full set of sashimi. Dip your favorite nigiri in wasabi to triple its value! And once you've eaten it all, finish your meal with all the pudding you've got! But be careful which sushi you allow your friends to take; it might be just what they need to beat you!","loc":["Greenfield"]},{"id":"24","title":"Yuri on Ice! (5hrs)","date":"2019-01-17","time":"17:00","mins":"60","loc":["Henry Ford"]},{"id":"25","title":"Welcome to ConFusion!","date":"2019-01-17","time":"17:00","mins":"60","desc":"Kids welcome tour of ConFusion.","loc":["KidFusion"]},{"id":"26","title":"Dragon's Den","date":"2019-01-17","time":"17:00","mins":"60","desc":"Join the Board of the Ann Arbor Science Fiction Association and pitch your idea to make the con even better! Impress the Board and get your idea funded to improve the con experience for everyone.","loc":["Ontario"],"people":[{"name":"Amy Sexsmith","id":"5"},{"name":"Anna Carey","id":"11"},{"name":"Allison Anderson","id":"4"},{"name":"Cylithria Dubois","id":"30"},{"name":"Eric Guy","id":"51"},{"name":"Brian Decker","id":"20"}]},{"id":"27","title":"We fit together like two pieces of a puzzle with your hand a perfect match for me","date":"2019-01-17","time":"17:00","mins":"60","desc":"No, this isn't about love. This panel is dedicated to doing puzzles and playing games with a deck of 52 cards","loc":["TeenFusion"]},{"id":"28","title":"Urban Fantasy and Paranormal Romance","date":"2019-01-17","time":"18:00","mins":"60","desc":"Urban Fantasy and Paranormal Romance have a lot in common: mythical creatures in modern settings, noir and crime fiction aesthetics, and, often, romantic plotlines. What distinguishes the two genres, and where to they overlap? How do they use their common elements to create different goals?","loc":["Allen Park"],"people":[{"name":"Andrew M. ‘Fish‘ Popowich","id":"9"},{"name":"Josef Matulich","id":"72"},{"name":"Michael Cieslak","id":"95"},{"name":"Delilah Dawson","id":"40"}]},{"id":"29","title":"The Future of Masculinity","date":"2019-01-17","time":"18:00","mins":"60","desc":"Masculinity and â€œmanlinessâ€ are social constructs, and like all social constructs, they evolve and change over time. How will our definitions of masculinity evolve over time? How can we portray positive visions of masculinity in speculative fiction?","loc":["Dearborn"],"people":[{"name":"Pablo Defendini","id":"107"},{"name":"Michael R. Underwood","id":"99"},{"name":"John Chu","id":"66"},{"name":"David Anthony Durham","id":"37"}]},{"id":"30","title":"Outlining Methods For Short and Long Fiction","date":"2019-01-17","time":"18:00","mins":"60","desc":"Outlines are a popular and powerful tool for planning out fiction, but the persuasive non-fiction outlining methods that many of us learned in school aren't particularly well-suited to storytelling. Many writers have developed their own methods for outlining, and many have tips you can adapt for your own use. Come learn about the outlining methods that work for our panel of writers, and where to find additional resources on how to make outlines work for you.","loc":["Erie"],"people":[{"name":"A. Merc Rustad","id":"2"},{"name":"Cherie Priest","id":"25"},{"name":"Mark Oshiro","id":"90"},{"name":"Ada Palmer","id":"3"}]},{"id":"31","title":"Codenames","date":"2019-01-17","time":"18:00","mins":"60","desc":"two teams compete to see who can contact all of their agents first. Use clues that could point to multiple words on the board to guess your teams words, but not the other teams!","loc":["Greenfield"]},{"id":"32","title":"Halls of the Minotaur (4hrs)","date":"2019-01-17","time":"18:00","mins":"60","desc":"A villainous minotaur has beset your small hamlet, raiding, killing, and even stealing children! A valiant paladin went after the beast but he has not returned. With no other options left five brave villagers decide to take matters into their own hands and end this villain's reign of terror once and for all!","loc":["Greenfield"]},{"id":"33","title":"Sparkly, Shiny Suncatchers!","date":"2019-01-17","time":"18:00","mins":"60","desc":"Make a suncatcher using jewels and glue. Will need time to dry.","loc":["KidFusion"]},{"id":"34","title":"Puns","date":"2019-01-17","time":"18:00","mins":"60","desc":"Some people love puns. Other people are wrong and hate fun. Our panel of experts discusses one of the greatest tools in the comedic toolbox.","loc":["Ontario"],"people":[{"name":"John Wiswell","id":"69"},{"name":"Clif Flynt","id":"28"},{"name":"Jon Skovron","id":"70"},{"name":"Nibedita Sen","id":"105"}]},{"id":"35","title":"Dinner Break","date":"2019-01-17","time":"18:00","mins":"60","desc":"\"Dummy, dummy, go out now and fill your tummy.\"","loc":["TeenFusion"]},{"id":"36","title":"So This Is Your First ConFusion (Fri)","date":"2019-01-17","time":"18:00","mins":"60","desc":"First time at ConFusion, or science fiction conventions in general? Join us to hear about the history of the convention and even a little tour of the con. We'll answer any questions you have (about the con; quantum physics questions are handled elsewhere).","loc":["Warren"]},{"id":"37","title":"Right Song, Right Time","date":"2019-01-17","time":"19:00","mins":"60","desc":"Whether it's a full concert or a few songs in a Filk circle, picking the perfect song for a given moment can be challenging. Panelists will talk about the many varied approaches to how they pick and arrange songs for a given setting, about giving song introductions, having potential backup songs prepared, and more.","loc":["Fairlane"],"people":[{"name":"Eric Distad","id":"50"},{"name":"Jen Distad","id":"58"}]},{"id":"38","title":"Codenames","date":"2019-01-17","time":"19:00","mins":"60","desc":"two teams compete to see who can contact all of their agents first. Use clues that could point to multiple words on the board to guess your teams words, but not the other teams!","loc":["Greenfield"]},{"id":"39","title":"Bedtime Snack and Story Time","date":"2019-01-17","time":"19:00","mins":"60","desc":"Grab your pjs and a blanket and join the KidFusion staff and friends for a bedtime snack and a fairy story.","loc":["KidFusion"]},{"id":"40","title":"Opening Ceremonies","date":"2019-01-17","time":"19:00","mins":"60","desc":"Welcome to Storming the ConFusion! Please join our ConChair and Guests of Honor Ada Palmer, Steve Macdonald, Jen Piatek, and David Stein, along with our Special Guests, courtesy of Subterranean Press, Joe Lansdale and Lewis Shiner! Hear about all the exciting stuff you can expect from them, and us, this weekend!","loc":["Michigan"],"people":[{"name":"Joe R. Lansdale","id":"64"},{"name":"Lewis Shiner","id":"85"},{"name":"Steve Macdonald","id":"123"},{"name":"Dr. Jennifer Piatek","id":"43"},{"name":"David M Stein","id":"39"},{"name":"DI","id":"31"},{"name":"Amy Sexsmith","id":"5"}]},{"id":"41","title":"D&D","date":"2019-01-17","time":"19:00","mins":"60","desc":"(Teens) Play D&D in the Teen Room. Previous experience is not required.","loc":["TeenFusion"]},{"id":"42","title":"Young Adult Authors in Conversation","date":"2019-01-17","time":"20:00","mins":"60","desc":"Our panel of authors of Young Adult fiction who write in different genres talk about their journey to publishing, their craft, and the future of YA.","loc":["Allen Park"],"people":[{"name":"Cassandra Morgan","id":"22"},{"name":"Stacey Filak","id":"121"},{"name":"Merrie Haskell","id":"94"},{"name":"Mark Oshiro","id":"90"}]},{"id":"43","title":"Dessert Reception","date":"2019-01-17","time":"20:00","mins":"60","desc":"Come enjoy desserts and mingle with our Guests of Honor and Subterranean Press's Special Guests!","loc":["ConSuite"],"people":[{"name":"Joe R. Lansdale","id":"64"},{"name":"Lewis Shiner","id":"85"},{"name":"Steve Macdonald","id":"123"},{"name":"Dr. Jennifer Piatek","id":"43"},{"name":"David M Stein","id":"39"},{"name":"DI","id":"31"}]},{"id":"44","title":"Food, Flavor, and Culture In Secondary Worlds","date":"2019-01-17","time":"20:00","mins":"60","desc":"We live in a world where food and flavor profiles are closely linked with culture and family--be it handed-down recipes or the smells and tastes of particular ingredients viscerally signalling â€œhome.â€ How can we incorporate distinct foods and food aesthetics into our secondary worlds to create a sense of place and culture? When is it the right choice to incorporate real-world foods that will be familiar to readers, and when is it better to invent new dishes?","loc":["Erie"],"people":[{"name":"Jessi Cole Jackson","id":"62"},{"name":"Dan Stout","id":"34"},{"name":"Ken Schrader","id":"80"}]},{"id":"45","title":"Red Dragon Inn","date":"2019-01-17","time":"20:00","mins":"60","desc":"You've defeated the dragon and returned to the inn to spend your well-earned gold. Prove that you can party harder than the rest of your party by being the last adventurer standing in the pub.","loc":["Greenfield"]},{"id":"46","title":"How To Design A Monster","date":"2019-01-17","time":"20:00","mins":"60","desc":"Authors have a vast and deep mythology to draw from when writing vampires, werewolves, and other mythological creatures. How do we choose which parts of their myths to incorporate into our own worlds? How do we incorporate new traits while still making them recognizable, and how do we avoid making our monsters derivative and stale? We'll talk about how to work out their appearance, limitations, social structures, and how they fit into the larger society of a fantasy world.","loc":["Ontario"],"people":[{"name":"John Wiswell","id":"69"},{"name":"A. Merc Rustad","id":"2"},{"name":"Tracy Townsend","id":"128"},{"name":"Petra Kuppers","id":"111"}]},{"id":"47","title":"Reading: Sean Martin, Anthony W. Eichenlaub","date":"2019-01-17","time":"20:00","mins":"60","loc":["Rotunda"],"people":[{"name":"Anthony W. Eichenlaub","id":"13"}]},{"id":"48","title":"Footnotes in Fiction","date":"2019-01-17","time":"20:00","mins":"60","desc":"While readers are accustomed to footnotes in translated and historical works, footnotes, endnotes, and other side-matter such as indexes pack powerful storytelling potential. Goldman used them to power the meta-story in The Princess Bride. Ursula K. Le Guin used the occasional footnote to define terms, and footnotes are popular in alt history and historical fiction for audiences of all ages. How can we use footnotes to best effect in our work, and how do we walk the line between entertaining flavortext and extraneous infodump?","loc":["Southfield"],"people":[{"name":"David John Baker","id":"38"},{"name":"Scott H. Andrews","id":"119"},{"name":"Anaea Lay","id":"7"},{"name":"Amy Sundberg","id":"6"}]},{"id":"49","title":"Concert by The Faithful Sidekicks","date":"2019-01-17","time":"21:00","mins":"60","desc":"The Faithful Sidekicks are the Acoustic Geek Rock/Filk duo of Eric and Jen Distad. They write and perform an eclectic mix of original catchy songs about the geeky stuff they love from comedic pop songs like \"Han Solo For President\" to love songs written in SQL Code, and everything in between. They have released two CDs, the most recent being \"Achievement Unlocked\".","loc":["Fairlane"],"people":[{"name":"Jen Distad","id":"58"}]},{"id":"50","title":"Red Dragon Inn","date":"2019-01-17","time":"21:00","mins":"60","desc":"You've defeated the dragon and returned to the inn to spend your well-earned gold. Prove that you can party harder than the rest of your party by being the last adventurer standing in the pub.","loc":["Greenfield"]},{"id":"51","title":"Torrent of Torment (2hrs)","date":"2019-01-17","time":"21:00","mins":"60","desc":"the adventures guild got a contract to recover a lost object while cleaning out the ruins of the undercity. A 4th level adventure.","loc":["Greenfield"]},{"id":"52","title":"Dance Party With DJ Scalzi","date":"2019-01-17","time":"21:00","mins":"60","desc":"Dance the night away with DJ Scalzi spinning the tunes!","loc":["Michigan"]},{"id":"53","title":"Friends of Bill W (Fri)","date":"2019-01-17","time":"21:00","mins":"60","loc":["Model T"]},{"id":"54","title":"Theme Circle: Hello Computer","date":"2019-01-17","time":"22:00","mins":"60","desc":"Songs about living with (or in spite of) Computer Technology and the Internet. Hosted by Jen and Eric Distad.","loc":["Fairlane"],"people":[{"name":"Jen Distad","id":"58"}]},{"id":"55","title":"Red Dragon Inn","date":"2019-01-17","time":"22:00","mins":"60","desc":"You've defeated the dragon and returned to the inn to spend your well-earned gold. Prove that you can party harder than the rest of your party by being the last adventurer standing in the pub.","loc":["Greenfield"]},{"id":"56","title":"Darling in the Franxx (5hrs)","date":"2019-01-17","time":"22:00","mins":"60","loc":["Henry Ford"]},{"id":"57","title":"Open Music Circle","date":"2019-01-17","time":"23:00","mins":"60","loc":["Fairlane"]},{"id":"58","title":"GranBlue Fantasy (5 hrs)","date":"2019-01-18","time":"03:00","mins":"60","loc":["Henry Ford"]},{"id":"59","title":"Frosty Fun Run!","date":"2019-01-18","time":"08:00","mins":"60","desc":"Urban Fantasy Author and inflatable dragon enthusiast Diana Rowland hosts her annual Fun Run around the hotel! Do what you can to make it a mile and win a medal!","loc":["Atrium"]},{"id":"60","title":"Geek Parent Meet Up (Early Risers)","date":"2019-01-18","time":"8:00","mins":"60","desc":"Join up with like-minded parents in the ConSuite for treats, juice boxes, and mutual support on the subject of raising kids in fandom! This one is for the early risers, up with babies and toddlers and other wakeful kids!","loc":["ConSuite"]},{"id":"61","title":"Radiant (4hrs)","date":"2019-01-18","time":"08:00","mins":"60","loc":["Henry Ford"]},{"id":"62","title":"Qelong (4hrs)","date":"2019-01-18","time":"09:00","mins":"60","desc":"Two barely conceivable beings have fought a war for a generation over Sajavedra, a barely legendary land far to the southeast. They wish to claim its rich harvests of souls and fields, its intricate networks of ley lines and temples, for their own. They have devastated it utterly. The land is ripe for plunder, if you are brave or lucky enough to do so.","loc":["Greenfield"]},{"id":"63","title":"Kaffeeklatsch with Music GOH Steve Macdonald","date":"2019-01-18","time":"09:00","mins":"60","desc":"Join Music Guest of Honor Steve Macdonald for a small-scale conversation and Q&A over cups of coffee or tea. Limit 10 attendees, sign up in Ops.","loc":["Model T"]},{"id":"64","title":"Open Room","date":"2019-01-18","time":"09:00","mins":"60","loc":["TeenFusion"]},{"id":"65","title":"Octopus and Ape","date":"2019-01-18","time":"10:00","mins":"60","desc":"We Want YOUR Opinion! Julie Lesnik, a ConFusion science track regular, is bringing her love of human evolution, bug eating, and all things biologically fascinating to YouTube in February 2019. Get a sneak peek at some of the content and provide feedback that will be used to make this channel great. Walk away with an Octopus and Ape badge ribbon and adorably awesome logo swag.","loc":["Allen Park"]},{"id":"66","title":"Geek Parent Meet Up","date":"2019-01-18","time":"10:00","mins":"60","desc":"Join up with like-minded parents in the ConSuite for treats, juice boxes, and mutual support on the subject of raising kids in fandom!","loc":["ConSuite"]},{"id":"67","title":"Beyond the Boilerplate","date":"2019-01-18","time":"10:00","mins":"60","desc":"So the cast of your comic strip has finally done it all. Met, got married, had kids, sent the kids to college, moved them out of the basement, and now return to the empty nest... So what next? What do you do when your virtual people have told their stories? The creators of three long-running comics--two of which have run for thirty or more years--will discuss the problem and the solutions they found. Discussion will follow.","loc":["Dearborn"],"people":[{"name":"BluRaven C. Houvener","id":"15"},{"name":"Kurt Erichsen","id":"81"}]},{"id":"68","title":"So This Is Your First ConFusion (Sat)","date":"2019-01-18","time":"10:00","mins":"60","desc":"First time at ConFusion, or science fiction conventions in general? Join us to hear about the history of the convention and even a little tour of the con. We'll answer any questions you have (about the con; quantum physics questions are handled elsewhere).","loc":["Erie"]},{"id":"69","title":"Kill Doctor Lucky","date":"2019-01-18","time":"10:00","mins":"60","desc":"In this notorious game, an inversion of Clue, you hate Doctor Lucky. Maybe he left you out of his will. Maybe he killed your pet rock. Whatever the reason, you want him dead. Unfortunately, so do the other players. Since you don't want to go to jail, you need to make your attempt in secret; if anybody can see you, whistle nonchalantly, and let the Doctor live ... until next time.","loc":["Greenfield"]},{"id":"70","title":"Tomb of Horrors (4hrs)","date":"2019-01-18","time":"10:00","mins":"60","desc":"A Dungeons and Dragons Classic updated for 5th Edition! Somewhere under a lost and lonely hill of grim and foreboding aspect lies a labyrinthine crypt. It is filled with terrible traps and not a few strange and ferocious monsters to slay the unwary. It is filled with rich treasures both precious and magical, but in addition to the aforementioned guardians, there is said to be a demi-lich who still wards his final haunt.","loc":["Greenfield"]},{"id":"71","title":"Wake Up Yoga","date":"2019-01-18","time":"10:00","mins":"60","desc":"Learn some yoga poses to get your day started","loc":["KidFusion"]},{"id":"72","title":"Kaffeeklatsch with Pro GOH Ada Palmer","date":"2019-01-18","time":"10:00","mins":"60","desc":"Join Guest of Honor Ada Palmer for a small-scale conversation and Q&A over cups of coffee or tea. Limit 10 attendees, sign up in Ops.","loc":["Model T"]},{"id":"73","title":"The Trouble With Susan (and Donna, and...)","date":"2019-01-18","time":"10:00","mins":"60","desc":"Many beloved genre stories don't treat their female characters well. Our genre is full of stories that punish female heroes with debasement and tragedy and unhappy endings, either implying or stating outright that the heroines with whom we identify were too ambitious for their own good. How do we reconcile our love for these stories and characters with the poison pills that come with them? Can we keep loving stories that don't love us back?","loc":["Ontario"],"people":[{"name":"Navah Wolfe","id":"104"},{"name":"Karen Osborne","id":"78"},{"name":"K. Lynne O‘Connor","id":"75"},{"name":"Cat Rambo","id":"23"}]},{"id":"74","title":"Reading: Jordan Kurella, Tim Boerger, Lucy A. Snyder","date":"2019-01-18","time":"10:00","mins":"60","loc":["Rotunda"],"people":[{"name":"Tim Boerger","id":"127"},{"name":"Lucy A. Snyder","id":"86"}]},{"id":"75","title":"Flash Fiction Improv","date":"2019-01-18","time":"10:00","mins":"60","desc":"Fast paced and quick witted, authors create stories in real time, \"round robin\" style, using prompts from the audience.","loc":["Southfield"],"people":[{"name":"Mur Lafferty","id":"101"},{"name":"Vanessa Ricci-Thode","id":"129"},{"name":"Suzanne Church","id":"124"}]},{"id":"76","title":"Out Beyond Pluto: New Horizons Visits the Kuiper Belt","date":"2019-01-18","time":"11:00","mins":"60","desc":"If all goes well, a few weeks before ConFusion, NASA's New Horizons spacecraft should have encountered the object known as 2014 MU69 or \"Ultima Thule.\" Discuss the science of Kuiper Belt Objects and (we hope) the results of the flyby.","loc":["Allen Park"],"people":[{"name":"Dr. Jennifer Piatek","id":"43"}]},{"id":"77","title":"The Craft of Episodic Storytelling","date":"2019-01-18","time":"11:00","mins":"60","desc":"From comics to serialized novels, episodic fiction has a long history in genre. Thanks to the convenience of the internet, it's experienced a resurgence, with episodic short fiction, web series, and episodic video games. What impact does serialization have on how writers approach plot, pacing, exposition, and characterization? What qualities make a story a good fit for serialization? What can you do in a serialized story more easily than in a non-serialized one? What becomes harder when serialization is in the mix?","loc":["Dearborn"],"people":[{"name":"Mur Lafferty","id":"101"},{"name":"Jennifer Mace","id":"60"},{"name":"Christian Klaver","id":"27"},{"name":"Nathan Rockwood","id":"103"}]},{"id":"78","title":"Reading: Ada Palmer","date":"2019-01-18","time":"11:00","mins":"60","loc":["Erie"]},{"id":"79","title":"Ghost Planets (4hrs)","date":"2019-01-18","time":"11:00","mins":"60","desc":"If you love the Fate system, or are interested in trying a new to you system, this session is for you. The characters are pre-made so the action can start right away! Play part of an archaeological exploration team in a universe where humanity is the only sentient race alive, that you know of. Remains of other races civilizations have been found, but no members of the races! There will be 5 adult player slots open","loc":["Greenfield"]},{"id":"80","title":"Crafting: Stress Balls","date":"2019-01-18","time":"11:00","mins":"60","desc":"Make your own stress ball using water beads and a balloon!","loc":["KidFusion"]},{"id":"81","title":"Camp Pencil Point","date":"2019-01-18","time":"11:00","mins":"60","desc":"Camp Pencil Point is a YouTube channel that teaches people, kids in particular, to draw with nonsense and tom foolery. It's also an event featured at ConFusion this year set up like a class room and the audience is invited to draw along. We provide the drawing materials, paper and pencil. There are drawing tutorials and drawing games. Plus there are prizes and art giveaways. Join us at ConFusion!","loc":["Model T"],"people":[{"name":"Joe Foo","id":"63"}]},{"id":"82","title":"Wakanda and The Political Power Of Alternate Presents","date":"2019-01-18","time":"11:00","mins":"60","desc":"While The Princess Bride and Black Panther both feature fictional countries, Black Panther uses its alternate history to challenge common narratives about colonialism, centering political commentary in its worldbuilding and plot. How can Science Fiction best use alternate history and alternate present to center and celebrate people whose real histories bear the scars of colonialism, genocide, and/or slavery? How can alternate histories that don't center on these themes avoid making light of, or reinforcing the inevitability of, these atrocities?","loc":["Ontario"],"people":[{"name":"LaShawn M. Wanak","id":"82"}]},{"id":"83","title":"Reading: A. Merc Rustad, Marissa Lingen, Annalee Flower Horne","date":"2019-01-18","time":"11:00","mins":"60","loc":["Rotunda"],"people":[{"name":"Marissa Lingen","id":"89"},{"name":"Annalee Flower Horne","id":"12"}]},{"id":"84","title":"Applying the Social Model of Disability to Genre Worldbuilding","date":"2019-01-18","time":"11:00","mins":"60","desc":"The social model of disability holds that whatever someone's physical traits, what renders a person disabled are physical and social structures not built to accommodate them. In The Princess Bride, Count Rugen's six fingers don't impede his swordsmanship--the fact that swords aren't built for his hand does. In the real world, what limits a wheelchair driver's freedom isn't their wheelchair, but spaces that aren't built for wheelchair access. We'll discuss how to incorporate the social model of disability into fantasy and science fiction world-building to build fictional worlds where people with wide ranges of physical traits and abilities have agency and self-determination, and talk about our favorite fictional worlds that are doing this right.","loc":["Southfield"],"people":[{"name":"Jordan Kurella","id":"71"},{"name":"Sandee Rodriguez","id":"115"},{"name":"Petra Kuppers","id":"111"}]},{"id":"85","title":"If there's ever a question about anything, you can always count on me to get it wrong.","date":"2019-01-18","time":"11:00","mins":"60","desc":"\"The Duchess set about studying Annette and shortly found her adversary's tragic flaw. Chocolate.\" Know a lot about Science Fiction? How about vines? Confident in your knowledge? Want to earn chocolate for knowing things? Then come visit us as we test how much you know and our ability to throw.","loc":["TeenFusion"]},{"id":"86","title":"Feline Nutrition 101","date":"2019-01-18","time":"12:00","mins":"60","desc":"Cats have been steadily growing in popularity for decades. Everyone from the likes of Hemingway to Freddie Mercury were all avid cat lovers. And as their popularity grows, so does our desire to learn how to care for our tiny tabby tigers. Join Cassandra Morgan, author and feline nutrition and behavior consultant as she walks you through her lecture on Feline Nutrition 101. Learn how to read a pet food label, what it means to be an Obligate Carnivore, settle the great Kibble vs Canned debate. It's going to be a purr-fectly meow-velous time!","loc":["Allen Park"]},{"id":"87","title":"Iron Artist (3hrs)","date":"2019-01-18","time":"12:00","mins":"60","desc":"Drawing/sculpture isn't usually a performance art, but Iron Artists show how they work while creating prepare a piece of art (or craft) on a topic related to Through the Looking Glass. Artists are working at their Artist Alley Tables or in the Lounge. Iron Art entries will been display in the lounge soon after 3 PM Saturday. Members of ConFusion vote on their favorites -- ballots will be available at Ops and in the Lounge from 3-5. Entries will be shown and winners announced at the Masquerade.","loc":["Atrium"],"people":[{"name":"BluRaven C. Houvener","id":"15"},{"name":"Emily Zelasko","id":"48"},{"name":"John Benson","id":"65"},{"name":"Melanie Brooks","id":"92"},{"name":"Sara Burnett","id":"116"},{"name":"Michael Kucharski","id":"98"},{"name":"Crystal Mielcarek","id":"29"},{"name":"Rachel Quinlan","id":"113"}]},{"id":"88","title":"How To Storm A Castle: Pre-Industrial Defenses Around The World","date":"2019-01-18","time":"12:00","mins":"60","desc":"How, precisely, do you storm a castle? Join our panel to discuss pre-industrial building defenses, their strengths and vulnerabilities, and how to get past them if you need to defeat the evil prince within.","loc":["Dearborn"],"people":[{"name":"Josef Matulich","id":"72"},{"name":"Scott H. Andrews","id":"119"},{"name":"Ada Palmer","id":"3"}]},{"id":"89","title":"Showing Your Work: Showcasing Research in Genre Fiction","date":"2019-01-18","time":"12:00","mins":"60","desc":"Authors are often cautioned to avoid info-dumps in our work: lengthy explanations of science and history have fallen out of fashion in favor of subtly weaving in relevant research without drawing attention to it. But William Goldman broke this rule throughout The Princess Bride; most memorably in Wesley's fight scene with Montoya, where the two spend the entire fight discussing real swordsmen who influenced the theory and practice of renaissance fencing. Panelists will discuss when it's a good idea to shine a light on your research, and recommend examples of research-dumps that manage to entertain and delight readers.","loc":["Erie"],"people":[{"name":"Lucy A. Snyder","id":"86"},{"name":"Lawrence M. Schoen","id":"84"},{"name":"Michael Cieslak","id":"95"},{"name":"Nino Cipri","id":"106"}]},{"id":"90","title":"Concert by Random Fractions","date":"2019-01-18","time":"12:00","mins":"60","desc":"This Chicago-area trio combines guitar, bass, keyboard, and smooth harmonies into a musical journey through life's quirky adventures and marvelous journeys with a sound that is part folk, part rock, and part something we can't quite define...but we know it's fun!","loc":["Fairlane"]},{"id":"91","title":"Villainous","date":"2019-01-18","time":"12:00","mins":"60","desc":"Disney Villainous is a light strategy game for up to 6 players featuring favorite Disney villains.","loc":["Greenfield"]},{"id":"92","title":"The Princess Bride (1.5hrs)","date":"2019-01-18","time":"12:00","mins":"60","loc":["Henry Ford"]},{"id":"93","title":"AFTERNOON BREAK","date":"2019-01-18","time":"12:00","mins":"60","desc":"KidFusion is closed for one hour in the afternoon.","loc":["KidFusion"]},{"id":"94","title":"Writers Talk About Anything BUT Writing","date":"2019-01-18","time":"12:00","mins":"60","desc":"Our panelists answer your burning questions on anything--except writing. Ask about cooking, motorcycle repair, science, the meaning of life, color theory, their favorite and least favorite airports--anything but writing! (accuracy of answers is not guaranteed).","loc":["Ontario"],"people":[{"name":"John Scalzi","id":"67"},{"name":"Delilah Dawson","id":"40"}]},{"id":"95","title":"Reading: Angus Watson, Dan Stout, Dyrk Ashton","date":"2019-01-18","time":"12:00","mins":"60","loc":["Rotunda"],"people":[{"name":"Dan Stout","id":"34"},{"name":"Dyrk Ashton","id":"45"}]},{"id":"96","title":"Political History As Setting in Science Fiction and Fantasy","date":"2019-01-18","time":"12:00","mins":"60","desc":"The history of Gildor is essential context for S. Morganstern's classic. Even in his abridged version, Goldman includes this background in footnotes so that readers will be able to fully appreciate the story. Whether we're writing a sweeping secondary-world epic, an alternate history, or futuristic science fiction, giving our worlds history helps them feel lived-in and real. Let's talk about our favorite worlds with deep histories, and how authors can weave historical information into the story in an engaging way that doesn't bog down the narrative with infodumps.","loc":["Southfield"],"people":[{"name":"Anaea Lay","id":"7"},{"name":"Carl Engle-Laird","id":"21"},{"name":"K.A. Doore","id":"76"},{"name":"K. Lynne O‘Connor","id":"75"},{"name":"Lewis Shiner","id":"85"}]},{"id":"97","title":"Lunch Break","date":"2019-01-18","time":"12:00","mins":"60","desc":"\"Dummy, dummy, go out now and fill your tummy.\"","loc":["TeenFusion"]},{"id":"98","title":"Mars in Fact and Fiction","date":"2019-01-18","time":"13:00","mins":"60","desc":"Mars looms large in science fiction, and in NASA's planetary exploration program. Listen to scientists and experts discuss the ways Mars has been explored in both scientific ways and by characters in science fiction.","loc":["Allen Park"],"people":[{"name":"Martin L. Shoemaker","id":"91"},{"name":"Dr. Jennifer Piatek","id":"43"}]},{"id":"99","title":"Hospitality, Sanctuary, and Refuge in Secondary Worlds","date":"2019-01-18","time":"13:00","mins":"60","desc":"Real-world cultures have wide-ranging rules and customs around how much hospitality we owe to strangers. What are our favorite examples of hospitality customs in science fiction and fantasy? How can we build realistic hospitality customs for secondary world cultures, and how can we use hospitality customs to add depth to our world-building or create challenges for our characters?","loc":["Dearborn"],"people":[{"name":"Eric Anderson","id":"49"},{"name":"Scott H. Andrews","id":"119"},{"name":"E.D.E. (Emily) Bell","id":"47"}]},{"id":"100","title":"What Computer Programming Can Teach Us About Writing","date":"2019-01-18","time":"13:00","mins":"60","desc":"Writing code and writing fiction may not seem to have a lot in common at the sentence level, but writers and programmers have to manage a lot of the same challenges. Come learn how to apply tools from software development, such as agile development, technical debt management, and code review, to the fiction writing process.","loc":["Erie"],"people":[{"name":"Pablo Defendini","id":"107"},{"name":"Jennifer Mace","id":"60"},{"name":"John Chu","id":"66"},{"name":"Cat Rambo","id":"23"}]},{"id":"101","title":"Workshop: ChordPro and You","date":"2019-01-18","time":"13:00","mins":"60","desc":"A beginning tutorial on the software that you can use to build your electronic songbook.","loc":["Fairlane"],"people":[{"name":"Daniel Gunderson","id":"36"}]},{"id":"102","title":"Villainous","date":"2019-01-18","time":"13:00","mins":"60","desc":"Disney Villainous is a light strategy game for up to 6 players featuring favorite Disney villains.","loc":["Greenfield"]},{"id":"103","title":"Origami for Everyone!","date":"2019-01-18","time":"13:00","mins":"60","desc":"Learn origami with our special guest","loc":["KidFusion"]},{"id":"104","title":"History of Detroit Fandom","date":"2019-01-18","time":"13:00","mins":"60","desc":"60 years have gone by since Detroit's one and only WorldCon, Detention, and it's been over 45 years since the first ConFusion. Now a whole 5 years have passed since Detroit's wildly successful NasFic, DetCon1. Come relive some of the highlights of Detroit convention history with Fan Guest of Honor David Stein, and bring your own memories to share!","loc":["Ontario"],"people":[{"name":"Bill Higgins","id":"14"},{"name":"David M Stein","id":"39"},{"name":"DI","id":"31"}]},{"id":"105","title":"Reading: Michael J. DeLuca, Clif, John Wiswell","date":"2019-01-18","time":"13:00","mins":"60","loc":["Rotunda"],"people":[{"name":"Michael J. DeLuca","id":"97"},{"name":"Clif Flynt","id":"28"}]},{"id":"106","title":"Joe R. Lansdale and Lewis Shiner on Story Ideas","date":"2019-01-18","time":"13:00","mins":"60","desc":"Joe and Lew have been kicking story ideas back and forth for years; the main reason because the originator didn't want to write it. Here they will discuss story ideas they didn't want to write, why they didn't work for them, and what makes a successful idea. How do they turn a scrap of an idea into a full blown story?","loc":["Southfield"],"people":[{"name":"Joe R. Lansdale","id":"64"},{"name":"Lewis Shiner","id":"85"}]},{"id":"107","title":"My name is Inigo Montoya, you killed my father, prepare to die","date":"2019-01-18","time":"13:00","mins":"60","desc":"Come learn to fence like Inigo Montoya, without the perils of the cliffside or the sharpness of a blade.","loc":["TeenFusion"]},{"id":"108","title":"AI for Better or Worse","date":"2019-01-18","time":"13:00","mins":"60","desc":"There's no doubt that Artificial Intelligence will play some part in our future, but is it good, bad, or both? Panelists will discuss the future of AI, some of its uses, and some of its dangers.","loc":["Warren"],"people":[{"name":"John Winkelman","id":"68"},{"name":"Derek Kunsken","id":"41"}]},{"id":"109","title":"Kakuriyo (4hrs)","date":"2019-01-18","time":"13:30","mins":"60","loc":["Henry Ford"]},{"id":"110","title":"Roleplaying 101","date":"2019-01-18","time":"14:00","mins":"60","desc":"So you want to get into roleplaying games! Great! What does it take to get started, and do you want to contribute as a player or as a game master? How do you plan a basic session, what makes a good character, and what are the common pitfalls that face novice players and GMs?","loc":["Allen Park"],"people":[{"name":"Stephanie Lorée","id":"122"},{"name":"Andrew M. ‘Fish‘ Popowich","id":"9"},{"name":"Brian Bay","id":"19"},{"name":"Dan Wells","id":"35"}]},{"id":"111","title":"The Stories We Pass Down","date":"2019-01-18","time":"14:00","mins":"60","desc":"The central conceit of The Princess Bride was that Goldman wanted to share S. Morgenstern's classic--his childhood favorite--with his own kid. This is a relatable experience for many readers. But many of us find ourselves in Goldman's shoes: trying to manage our disappointment that our kid could barely choke down the first chapter of our childhood favorite. How do we decide whether a book we loved as a kid is a good fit for our own kids, and when they're old enough to appreciate it? How can we share our favorites with our kids in a way that respects their individual taste?","loc":["Dearborn"],"people":[{"name":"Stacey Filak","id":"121"},{"name":"Michael Cieslak","id":"95"},{"name":"Ken Schrader","id":"80"},{"name":"David Anthony Durham","id":"37"}]},{"id":"112","title":"Fan GOH Induction","date":"2019-01-18","time":"14:00","mins":"60","desc":"This annual ceremony welcomes the latest Fan Guest of Honor into the hallowed halls of those who came before!","loc":["Fairlane"],"people":[{"name":"David M Stein","id":"39"},{"name":"DI","id":"31"}]},{"id":"113","title":"Downforce","date":"2019-01-18","time":"14:00","mins":"60","desc":"card-driven bidding, racing & betting game. Players first bid to own the six cars in the race, then play cards from their hand to race around the track. Timing is key to victory.","loc":["Greenfield"]},{"id":"114","title":"Remnants in Wetlands (4hrs)","date":"2019-01-18","time":"14:00","mins":"60","desc":"Roughly 15 years after the events of Pokemon Super Mystery Dungeon, a team of adventurers from the exploration guild is hired by a Pikachu client to help protect her on an expedition to find a hidden temple deep in a wetland dungeon area, but is there more to this quest then their client is telling them? Pre-generated characters and dice will be provided by the GM and no previous experience with the Genesys RPG system is required.","loc":["Greenfield"]},{"id":"115","title":"Princess Buttercup's Royal Tea","date":"2019-01-18","time":"14:00","mins":"60","desc":"Join us for a royal tea party with our special guests!","loc":["KidFusion"]},{"id":"116","title":"Concert by Ada Palmer and Friends","date":"2019-01-18","time":"14:00","mins":"60","desc":"A special 90-minute set by our Author GoH and her friends, featuring both music of the Renaissance and Ada's Viking-themed works.","loc":["Michigan"],"people":[{"name":"Lauren Schiller","id":"83"},{"name":"Michael J Mellas","id":"96"}]},{"id":"117","title":"Reading: Michael R. Underwood, Ferrett Steinmetz, Patrick S. Tomlinson","date":"2019-01-18","time":"14:00","mins":"60","loc":["Rotunda"],"people":[{"name":"Ferrett Steinmetz","id":"52"},{"name":"Patrick S. Tomlinson","id":"109"}]},{"id":"118","title":"Fairytale Retellings in the Modern Market","date":"2019-01-18","time":"14:00","mins":"60","desc":"Fairytales are a common inspiration for stories and novels, especially in YA. What is it about fairy tales that make us tell and retell them? How do these stories speak to us and why?","loc":["Southfield"],"people":[{"name":"Jessi Cole Jackson","id":"62"},{"name":"Amy Sundberg","id":"6"},{"name":"Jeffrey Chapman","id":"57"}]},{"id":"119","title":"You're an enemy of art and I pity your ignorance, Domingo said.\"","date":"2019-01-18","time":"14:00","mins":"60","desc":"Come color with us and love the art that you can create","loc":["TeenFusion"]},{"id":"120","title":"American Horror Story","date":"2019-01-18","time":"14:00","mins":"60","desc":"An ambitious experiment in anthology television has carried on to its improbably nine millionth season. What's working, what isn't, and what the actual heck is going on?","loc":["Warren"],"people":[{"name":"Sandee Rodriguez","id":"115"},{"name":"Navah Wolfe","id":"104"}]},{"id":"121","title":"Paint and Take (6hrs)","date":"2019-01-18","time":"15:00","mins":"60","loc":["Atrium"]},{"id":"122","title":"Reading: John Scalzi","date":"2019-01-18","time":"15:00","mins":"60","loc":["Dearborn"]},{"id":"123","title":"Autograph Session (3pm)","date":"2019-01-18","time":"15:00","mins":"60","desc":"Meet your favorite authors and get your books signed! Limit 3 items per person, please.","loc":["Erie"],"people":[{"name":"Angus Watson","id":"10"},{"name":"Anthony W. Eichenlaub","id":"13"},{"name":"Cat Rambo","id":"23"},{"name":"Diana Rowland","id":"42"},{"name":"Dyrk Ashton","id":"45"},{"name":"Jason Sanford","id":"55"},{"name":"Joe R. Lansdale","id":"64"},{"name":"Josef Matulich","id":"72"}]},{"id":"124","title":"Lords of Waterdeep","date":"2019-01-18","time":"15:00","mins":"60","desc":"A D&D themed worker placement game. Very easy to play, and perhaps one of the purest worker placement games on the market.","loc":["Greenfield"]},{"id":"125","title":"The Reunion (4hrs)","date":"2019-01-18","time":"15:00","mins":"60","desc":"You were once the students of Anchor Charter Acadamies. It has been a decade or more since you last set foot in now crumbling edifice and now the institution is having a school reunion. Why go back to the school that was abusive and traumatizing? Yes, why go back indeed?","loc":["Greenfield"]},{"id":"126","title":"Farmboy, Fetch My... (Scavenger Hunt)","date":"2019-01-18","time":"15:00","mins":"60","desc":"Princess Buttercup has left some things around ConFusion. Let's see if we can find them all!","loc":["KidFusion"]},{"id":"127","title":"Reading: Cherie Priest, Cassandra Morgan, LaShawn M. Wanak","date":"2019-01-18","time":"15:00","mins":"60","loc":["Rotunda"],"people":[{"name":"Cassandra Morgan","id":"22"},{"name":"LaShawn M. Wanak","id":"82"}]},{"id":"128","title":"She-Ra, Old and New","date":"2019-01-18","time":"15:00","mins":"60","desc":"She-Ra has returned to significant acclaim, and accompanied by other Princesses of Power. Has the reboot captured something new in its portrayals of Adora, Catra, and the rest of the cast? What did the original do well, and in what ways might it have been ripe for the reboot treatment?","loc":["Southfield"],"people":[{"name":"Yanni Kuznia","id":"130"},{"name":"Vanessa Ricci-Thode","id":"129"}]},{"id":"129","title":"Inconcievable Cookies!","date":"2019-01-18","time":"15:00","mins":"60","desc":"Come join us for an hour and decorate cookies to be inconceivable!","loc":["TeenFusion"]},{"id":"130","title":"Stargate SG-1 Retrospective","date":"2019-01-18","time":"16:00","mins":"60","desc":"It has been over 20 years since Stargate SG-1 showed up on our screens, and over 10 years since it left. Along the way, it spun off two other series, and a limited run prequel series last year. What made it great, and why did it resonate with so many people? What impact has it made on genre television and movies?","loc":["Allen Park"],"people":[{"name":"Keith Hughes","id":"79"},{"name":"Julayne Hughes","id":"73"},{"name":"Julie Winningham","id":"74"}]},{"id":"131","title":"Autograph Session (4pm)","date":"2019-01-18","time":"16:00","mins":"60","desc":"Meet your favorite authors and get your books signed! Limit 3 items per person, please.","loc":["Erie"],"people":[{"name":"Cassandra Morgan","id":"22"},{"name":"Cherie Priest","id":"25"},{"name":"Delilah Dawson","id":"40"},{"name":"Derek Kunsken","id":"41"},{"name":"E. D. E Bell","id":"46"},{"name":"Ferrett Steinmetz","id":"52"},{"name":"James L. Sutter","id":"54"},{"name":"John Scalzi","id":"67"}]},{"id":"132","title":"Jamming","date":"2019-01-18","time":"16:00","mins":"60","desc":"What makes a good jam session? What can you expect to happen, and how can you be ready for it?","loc":["Fairlane"],"people":[{"name":"Daniel Gunderson","id":"36"},{"name":"Cathy McManamon","id":"24"}]},{"id":"133","title":"Dice Forge","date":"2019-01-18","time":"16:00","mins":"60","desc":"Dice Forge is a development game featuring innovative mechanics based on dice with removable faces. In this dice crafting game, players build their own dice to gain resources to purchase upgrades.","loc":["Greenfield"]},{"id":"134","title":"Game On!","date":"2019-01-18","time":"16:00","mins":"60","desc":"Our friend Meri is joining us to play some kid-friendly games.","loc":["KidFusion"]},{"id":"135","title":"Reading: Tracy Townsend, Josef Matulich, Mackenzie Flohr","date":"2019-01-18","time":"16:00","mins":"60","loc":["Rotunda"],"people":[{"name":"Josef Matulich","id":"72"},{"name":"Mackenzie Flohr","id":"87"}]},{"id":"136","title":"Writing Humor in Science Fiction and Fantasy","date":"2019-01-18","time":"16:00","mins":"60","desc":"The Princess Bride is a classic of fantasy humor. What makes humor in speculative fiction work? What \"funny books\" really aren't? Let's look at American vs. British humor, which topics have aged well (or not so well!), short form vs. novels, and all the other things that make speculative humor more than pies in the face for elves.","loc":["Southfield"],"people":[{"name":"Tim Boerger","id":"127"},{"name":"Marissa Lingen","id":"89"},{"name":"Clif Flynt","id":"28"},{"name":"Joe R. Lansdale","id":"64"}]},{"id":"137","title":"Open Room","date":"2019-01-18","time":"16:00","mins":"60","loc":["TeenFusion"]},{"id":"138","title":"Let's Talk Season 2: Computer Science!","date":"2019-01-18","time":"16:00","mins":"60","desc":"A lighthearted talk on a hard science topics with smart and funny people. Let's Talk: Computer Science will chuckle through the collapse of society as we know it. Come hear how silicon makes better decisions than carbon, protons as data, why you don't need to be Slytherin to study Python, and what we are going to do with the leisure time we will have in 2025.","loc":["Warren"],"people":[{"name":"John Winkelman","id":"68"},{"name":"Anthony W. Eichenlaub","id":"13"}]},{"id":"139","title":"Reboot Fever!","date":"2019-01-18","time":"17:00","mins":"60","desc":"The concept of a reboot is nothing particularly new, but the trend in them is not limited to the underperforming properties, like Fantastic Four, or the barely remembered, but beloved classics are getting the treatment as well. Is this a plague that must be eradicated, a harbinger of the death of culture, a necessary refreshing of shared myths, or something else entirely? What's being done well, and what less well?","loc":["Allen Park"],"people":[{"name":"Marie S. Bilodeau","id":"88"}]},{"id":"140","title":"New Trends in Post-Collapse Fiction","date":"2019-01-18","time":"17:00","mins":"60","desc":"The prospect of a world where the march of social and technological progress has drastically reversed course seems a lot closer than it used to be. What has changed in the way we imagine post-collapse futures? How do post-collapse futures of the past and present exist in conversation with the social and political worlds in which they were written?","loc":["Dearborn"],"people":[{"name":"Andrea Johnson","id":"8"},{"name":"Michael J. DeLuca","id":"97"},{"name":"Petra Kuppers","id":"111"},{"name":"Anaea Lay","id":"7"}]},{"id":"141","title":"Raiders of the North Sea (2hrs)","date":"2019-01-18","time":"17:00","mins":"60","desc":"As Viking warriors, players seek to impress the Chieftain by raiding unsuspecting settlements. Players will need to assemble a crew, collect provisions and journey north to plunder gold, iron and livestock. There is glory to be found in battle, even at the hands of the Valkyrie. So gather your warriors, it's raiding season!","loc":["Greenfield"]},{"id":"142","title":"EVENING BREAK","date":"2019-01-18","time":"17:00","mins":"60","desc":"KidFusion is closed for two hours in the evening.","loc":["KidFusion"]},{"id":"143","title":"Concert by Tom Smith","date":"2019-01-18","time":"17:00","mins":"60","desc":"The world's fastest filker joins us again, for an hour of favorites old and new.","loc":["Michigan"]},{"id":"144","title":"Reading: Martin L. Shoemaker, Paul Kemner, Jennifer Mace","date":"2019-01-18","time":"17:00","mins":"60","loc":["Rotunda"],"people":[{"name":"Jennifer Mace","id":"60"},{"name":"Martin L. Shoemaker","id":"91"}]},{"id":"145","title":"Mostly Dead: The Problem of Death and Not-Quite-Death in SFF","date":"2019-01-18","time":"17:00","mins":"60","desc":"The frequency of resurrections or \"they died, but they didn't\" moments in SFF is (if one wishes to be kind) statistically unlikely. In this panel, we'll discuss various stories where death, death and resurrection, or false deaths play a key role in the narrative. How does the bloody ruthlessness of a series like Martin's Song of Ice and Fire change which characters \"get\" to die, and who stays dead? What are our favorite \"return to life\" moments? Which ones don't really work and why? And what must a writer do to make these moments serve the story and their audience?","loc":["Southfield"],"people":[{"name":"Angus Watson","id":"10"},{"name":"Jason Sanford","id":"55"},{"name":"Tracy Townsend","id":"128"},{"name":"Dan Wells","id":"35"}]},{"id":"146","title":"Teen Iron Artist","date":"2019-01-18","time":"17:00","mins":"60","desc":"An art competition for teens, judged by teens","loc":["TeenFusion"]},{"id":"147","title":"Let's Talk Season 2: Physics!","date":"2019-01-18","time":"17:00","mins":"60","desc":"A lighthearted talk on a hard science topics with smart and funny people. Let's Talk: Physics will dive deep into the building blocks of the Universe, the end of space, the future of materials, and will try not to giggle while discussing Super G-Strings.","loc":["Warren"],"people":[{"name":"David John Baker","id":"38"},{"name":"Bill Higgins","id":"14"},{"name":"Karen Burnham","id":"77"}]},{"id":"148","title":"Metafiction and S. Morgenstern","date":"2019-01-18","time":"18:00","mins":"60","desc":"Let's think about William Goldman's abridgment of S. Morgenstern's classic novel in the context of the film, Morgenstern's other surviving work, The Silent Gondoliers, and other classic metafictional/postmodern fantasy texts like Peter Beagle's The Last Unicorn, Michael Ende's The Neverending Story, Pratchett's Discworld, Angela Carter's The Bloody Chamber. How do these works compel our imaginations so effectively while also constantly undermining themselves with tongue firmly in cheek? Where did this kind of self-conscious mythmaking originate, and what's its modern legacy? How has fantasy changed because of it?","loc":["Allen Park"],"people":[{"name":"Sarah E. Gibbons","id":"117"},{"name":"John Chu","id":"66"},{"name":"K. Lynne O‘Connor","id":"75"}]},{"id":"149","title":"If you liked that, try this!","date":"2019-01-18","time":"18:00","mins":"60","desc":"Our well-read panel will give you personalized book recommendations based on things you've read and loved.","loc":["Dearborn"],"people":[{"name":"John Winkelman","id":"68"},{"name":"Andrea Johnson","id":"8"},{"name":"Karen Osborne","id":"78"},{"name":"Sarah Hans","id":"118"}]},{"id":"150","title":"Fandom Year in Review","date":"2019-01-18","time":"18:00","mins":"60","desc":"A lot has changed in the past year. The Doctor is back, three-time winner at the Hugos, and so much more. New books, new movies, new everything in 2018, so let's get together and talk about it!","loc":["Erie"],"people":[{"name":"Mackenzie Flohr","id":"87"},{"name":"Jeannie Szarama","id":"56"},{"name":"Derek Kunsken","id":"41"}]},{"id":"151","title":"Masquerade Muster","date":"2019-01-18","time":"18:00","mins":"60","desc":"Mandatory for all competitive entries in the Masquerade. Assemble to muster for the parade, be viewed by the judges, and have optional workmanship judging done. Competitors may enter as Novice, Journeyman, Master or Junior levels. Please be on time. Exhibition entries may attend the Muster or just join the parade, ending at the Masquerade. Pre-Registration for the Masquerade is STRONGLY encouraged. Sign up at OPS.","loc":["Fairlane"]},{"id":"152","title":"Sea Cove of Last Light (4hrs)","date":"2019-01-18","time":"18:00","mins":"60","desc":"You were once the students of Anchor Charter Acadamies. It has been a decade or more since you last set foot in now crumbling edifice and now the institution is having a school reunion. Why go back to the school that was abusive and traumatizing? Yes, why go back indeed?","loc":["Greenfield"]},{"id":"153","title":"Reading: Michael Cieslak, Ken Schrader, Jon Skovron","date":"2019-01-18","time":"18:00","mins":"60","loc":["Rotunda"],"people":[{"name":"Ken Schrader","id":"80"},{"name":"Jon Skovron","id":"70"}]},{"id":"154","title":"The Princess Bride (1.5hrs)","date":"2019-01-18","time":"18:30","mins":"60","loc":["Henry Ford"]},{"id":"155","title":"To the Pain: On Making Characters Struggle","date":"2019-01-18","time":"19:00","mins":"60","desc":"Sometimes you can't kill your protagonists outright ... but you can definitely put them through a lot. How do writers use different kinds of \"pain\" to craft better stories around their characters? At what point does a writer push their characters too much? And is it possible to create tension and conflict with minimal struggle?","loc":["Allen Park"],"people":[{"name":"Angus Watson","id":"10"},{"name":"Brandon Crilly","id":"18"},{"name":"Daan Wells","id":"33"}]},{"id":"156","title":"Sleeping In Light: A Look Back At Babylon 5","date":"2019-01-18","time":"19:00","mins":"60","desc":"Babylon 5 has been off the air for twenty years. Come join us to reminisce about the best parts, reconsider the parts that haven't aged so well, and cook up theories of what B5 could look like for a modern audience.","loc":["Erie"],"people":[{"name":"Michael R. Underwood","id":"99"},{"name":"Scott H. Andrews","id":"119"},{"name":"Natalie Luhrs","id":"102"}]},{"id":"157","title":"Terraforming Mars (3hrs)","date":"2019-01-18","time":"19:00","mins":"60","desc":"Initiate projects to raise temperature, oxygen level, and ocean coverage until the environment of Mars is habitable. Compete to accomplish the most terraforming, and for best locations on Mars.","loc":["Greenfield"]},{"id":"158","title":"The Stygian Garden of Abelia Prem (4hrs)","date":"2019-01-18","time":"19:00","mins":"60","desc":"Long ago a woman of wealth and nobility decided to build the greatest garden the world had ever heard of. Legend told of her being obsessed with a fabled rose that could bring back the dead to life and she poured all of her efforts to cultivate such a flower. Now her estate lays abandoned and rumors are that it is haunted, or worse! But, if the legends are true, such a rose would be invaluable, and perhaps it could be yours.","loc":["Greenfield"]},{"id":"159","title":"Pajama/Pizza Party","date":"2019-01-18","time":"19:00","mins":"60","desc":"THIS IS A PAID EVENT. Come ready to party in your pajamas! We will have Pizza, pop, popcorn along with movies, games and crafts. Register for this event at Registration by 12:00 PM Saturday. (5 HOURS)","loc":["KidFusion"]},{"id":"160","title":"Masquerade","date":"2019-01-18","time":"19:00","mins":"60","desc":"Come see - or show off - the best costumes of the night! Judges will scrutinize. Crowds will cheer. Audiences will swoon. Honors will be awarded","loc":["Michigan"]},{"id":"161","title":"Reading: Petra Kuppers, Anaea Lay, John Chu","date":"2019-01-18","time":"19:00","mins":"60","loc":["Rotunda"],"people":[{"name":"Anaea Lay","id":"7"},{"name":"John Chu","id":"66"}]},{"id":"162","title":"Communication During the Apocalypse","date":"2019-01-18","time":"19:00","mins":"60","desc":"Losing the internet has become a shorthand for the apocalypse in science fiction. When the internet goes down, what other options might we have? From Ham Radio to the postal service to Incan knots carried by trained birds, does losing the internet have to mean instant disaster?","loc":["Warren"],"people":[{"name":"Andrea Johnson","id":"8"},{"name":"Ken Schrader","id":"80"},{"name":"Bill Higgins","id":"14"}]},{"id":"163","title":"Murder, Meanness, and Other Solutions from Deep in the Edit Mines: How to Help Fix Each Other's Work Without Taking Over.","date":"2019-01-18","time":"20:00","mins":"60","desc":"How can we best use creative teamwork in solo projects? When your writing friends are stuck, where's the line between helpful and pushy? Is murder really the answer to every problem--and is it sometimes helpful to have a friend come through the door of your manuscript with a gun in hand when you don't know what to do next?","loc":["Allen Park"],"people":[{"name":"Jennifer Mace","id":"60"},{"name":"K.A. Doore","id":"76"}]},{"id":"164","title":"Let's Talk Season 2: Biology!","date":"2019-01-18","time":"20:00","mins":"60","desc":"A lighthearted talk on a hard science topics with smart and funny people. Let's Talk: Biology is about eating bugs vs eating people, how overblown CRISPR is, how soon can you pet a Triceratops, and what superbug is next on the horizon and how we will beat it.","loc":["Dearborn"],"people":[{"name":"Sandee Rodriguez","id":"115"},{"name":"Derek Kunsken","id":"41"},{"name":"Dr. Julie Lesnik","id":"44"}]},{"id":"165","title":"Inconceivable! Establishing Narrative Credibility in SFF","date":"2019-01-18","time":"20:00","mins":"60","desc":"The best science fiction and fantasy is often based around bizarre, alien worlds or premises, but these always need to be relatable to the reader. How do writers make the incredible credible? What effective tricks do we see our favorite authors pulling off, and which ones don't work on us as readers?","loc":["Erie"],"people":[{"name":"Angus Watson","id":"10"},{"name":"Brandon Crilly","id":"18"},{"name":"Marie S. Bilodeau","id":"88"},{"name":"Patrick Nielsen Hayden","id":"108"}]},{"id":"166","title":"That Time I Got Reincarnated as a Slime (4hrs)","date":"2019-01-18","time":"20:00","mins":"60","loc":["Henry Ford"]},{"id":"167","title":"Concert by Steve Macdonald","date":"2019-01-18","time":"20:00","mins":"60","desc":"Steve's been away for a while, living in Germany, so this is a rare chance to enjoy his songwriting, singing, and guitar work. You don't want to miss it!","loc":["Michigan"]},{"id":"168","title":"Ada Palmer Spoilers Reading","date":"2019-01-18","time":"20:00","mins":"60","desc":"Spoilers ahoy! Unlike Guest of Honor Ada Palmer's earlier reading, this one will be rife with spoilers, so proceed at your own caution!","loc":["Ontario"]},{"id":"169","title":"Reading: Karen Osborne, Keith Hughes, E.D.E. (Emily) Bell","date":"2019-01-18","time":"20:00","mins":"60","loc":["Rotunda"],"people":[{"name":"Keith Hughes","id":"79"},{"name":"E.D.E. (Emily) Bell","id":"47"}]},{"id":"170","title":"What Makes A Magic System Feel Satisfying?","date":"2019-01-18","time":"20:00","mins":"60","desc":"Some magic systems work with intense rules, and others run on vague hints and mystery. What makes either version work for a given work of fiction?","loc":["Southfield"],"people":[{"name":"Andrew M. ‘Fish‘ Popowich","id":"9"},{"name":"James L. Sutter","id":"54"},{"name":"Ferrett Steinmetz","id":"52"},{"name":"Christian Klaver","id":"27"}]},{"id":"171","title":"Fortunately for all concerned save the sharks, it was around this time that the moon came out.","date":"2019-01-18","time":"20:00","mins":"60","desc":"The Teenfusion room will have pizza and be open to teens aged 14-19 at this time.","loc":["TeenFusion"]},{"id":"172","title":"Phineas & Ferb Singalong","date":"2019-01-18","time":"21:00","mins":"60","desc":"There's 104 days of summer vacation... and we're going to singalong with a whole ton of songs from Phineas & Ferb in just an hour (or so).","loc":["Allen Park"]},{"id":"173","title":"Friends of Bill W (Sat)","date":"2019-01-18","time":"21:00","mins":"60","loc":["Model T"]},{"id":"174","title":"Theme Circle: The Shallow End","date":"2019-01-18","time":"22:00","mins":"60","desc":"A welcoming place for those who would like to sing something, but lack experience and confidence. Any type of material or performance is welcome. No recordings.","loc":["Fairlane"]},{"id":"175","title":"Open Music Circle","date":"2019-01-18","time":"23:00","mins":"60","loc":["Fairlane"]},{"id":"176","title":"Fate/Apocrypha (5hrs)","date":"2019-01-19","time":"00:00","mins":"60","loc":["Henry Ford"]},{"id":"177","title":"In Another World with My Smartphone (5hrs)","date":"2019-01-19","time":"05:00","mins":"60","loc":["Henry Ford"]},{"id":"178","title":"Argent the Consortium (3hrs)","date":"2019-01-19","time":"09:00","mins":"60","desc":"A game that is about becoming the next head of a magical college. To do so though is harder than it seems as the people voting on this are all looking for different things and most of them are unknown at the beginning of the game. It is a worker placement game with a huge dose of magical chaos and mayhem.","loc":["Greenfield"]},{"id":"179","title":"Kaffeeklatsch with Fan GOH David Stein","date":"2019-01-19","time":"09:00","mins":"60","desc":"Join Fan Guest of Honor David Stein for a small-scale conversation and Q&A over cups of coffee or tea. Limit 10 attendees, sign up in Ops.","loc":["Model T"]},{"id":"180","title":"Reading: Eric Anderson","date":"2019-01-19","time":"09:00","mins":"60","loc":["Rotunda"]},{"id":"181","title":"Oceanos","date":"2019-01-19","time":"10:00","mins":"60","desc":"Each player pilots her own submarine trying to spot the most underwater species and the largest coral reef, sending scuba-divers after forgotten treasures, collecting precious crystals to upgrade their ship and to escape the fearsome kraken's gaze...","loc":["Greenfield"]},{"id":"182","title":"Raiders of Pertalo (4hrs)","date":"2019-01-19","time":"10:00","mins":"60","desc":"During the spring equinox, on the Ides of the Falcon, the peaceful village on Lake Pertalo readies itself for the Fertility Feast of Agnor in celebration of a long winter coming to an end. All preparation comes to a sudden halt, however, when the community is overrun by an enemy that disappears as quickly as it arrived. Many are killed or wounded, but it soon becomes clear that this was not the goal of the raiders ... All of the village's children are now gone, apparently carried off in the chaos of the attack. As the characters begin to search for the missing children, they will discover a plot far more sinister than any of them had imagined ... and possibly be destroyed by it.","loc":["Greenfield"]},{"id":"183","title":"SAO Alternative: GGO (5hrs)","date":"2019-01-19","time":"10:00","mins":"60","loc":["Henry Ford"]},{"id":"184","title":"Wake Up Yoga","date":"2019-01-19","time":"10:00","mins":"60","desc":"Learn some yoga poses to get your day started","loc":["KidFusion"]},{"id":"185","title":"Black Gate Magazine Interviews GoH Ada Palmer","date":"2019-01-19","time":"10:00","mins":"60","desc":"Black Gate columnist and author Brandon Crilly sits down for a live interview with Pro GoH Ada Palmer, to discuss Terra Ignota, mythology, philosophy and looking ahead to the future.","loc":["Michigan"],"people":[{"name":"Ada Palmer","id":"3"}]},{"id":"186","title":"Kaffeeklatsch with Science GOH Jen Piatek","date":"2019-01-19","time":"10:00","mins":"60","desc":"Join Science Guest of Honor Jen Piatek for a small-scale conversation and Q&A over cups of coffee or tea. Limit 10 attendees, sign up in Ops.","loc":["Model T"]},{"id":"187","title":"Reading: K.A. Doore, Sarah Hans, Derek Kunsken","date":"2019-01-19","time":"10:00","mins":"60","loc":["Rotunda"],"people":[{"name":"Sarah Hans","id":"118"},{"name":"Derek Kunsken","id":"41"}]},{"id":"188","title":"never get involved in a land war in Asia, but do try their snacks","date":"2019-01-19","time":"10:00","mins":"60","desc":"Come join us as we delve into the world of Asian snacks, from candy to crisps","loc":["TeenFusion"]},{"id":"189","title":"How Fears Shape Superstitions","date":"2019-01-19","time":"11:00","mins":"60","desc":"From black cats-as-familiars to the number 13 being bad, all modern beliefs are rooted in folklore and ancient traditions that have been affected by political and social mores. Panelists will share examples and then discuss whether or not these powerful beliefs are harmful or helpful.","loc":["Allen Park"],"people":[{"name":"Lucy A. Snyder","id":"86"},{"name":"Sarah E. Gibbons","id":"117"},{"name":"Nino Cipri","id":"106"},{"name":"Monica Valentinelli","id":"100"}]},{"id":"190","title":"Superhero Fiction As A Case Study In Balancing Grit and Hope","date":"2019-01-19","time":"11:00","mins":"60","desc":"Since the eighties, we've seen a trend towards using more violence and darker storylines to attract a more mature audience to comics. But we're also seeing a growing fatigue for these dark visions of heroism, with more hopeful heroes hitting the scene and parodies such as Deadpool turning brooding and bleeding into a punchline. What lessons can we take from comics in how to strike the right tonal balance in our work? Who's using grit well? Who are our favorite hopeful heroes, and how do their creators deliver optimism without cheese?","loc":["Dearborn"],"people":[{"name":"Eric Anderson","id":"49"},{"name":"Sandee Rodriguez","id":"115"},{"name":"A. Merc Rustad","id":"2"},{"name":"BluRaven C. Houvener","id":"15"}]},{"id":"191","title":"ConFusion Wants You!","date":"2019-01-19","time":"11:00","mins":"60","desc":"Running ConFusion can take a lot of work, not just during the weekend, but over the course of the year leading up to it. We're always looking for new people to help, whether it's laying out this very program book, tweaking the website, or contributing programming ideas. Join us and let us know how to help, and hear from some of the people who do the work now to make it all happen!","loc":["Erie"],"people":[{"name":"Cylithria Dubois","id":"30"},{"name":"Eric Guy","id":"51"}]},{"id":"192","title":"7 Wonders","date":"2019-01-19","time":"11:00","mins":"60","desc":"You are the leader of one of the 7 great cities of the Ancient World. Gather resources, develop commercial routes, affirm your military supremacy. Build your city and erect an architectural wonder.","loc":["Greenfield"]},{"id":"193","title":"Sunday Morning Anime","date":"2019-01-19","time":"11:00","mins":"60","desc":"Come and watch youth-appropriate anime with friends.","loc":["KidFusion"]},{"id":"194","title":"Cosplaying 101","date":"2019-01-19","time":"11:00","mins":"60","desc":"What do you need to know about the ins and outs of cosplaying? An informational presentation from longtime ConFusion member Brian Bay!","loc":["Ontario"]},{"id":"195","title":"Reading: Mark Oshiro, Nibedita Sen","date":"2019-01-19","time":"11:00","mins":"60","loc":["Rotunda"],"people":[{"name":"Nibedita Sen","id":"105"}]},{"id":"196","title":"Tense and Point of View in Fantasy Today","date":"2019-01-19","time":"11:00","mins":"60","desc":"Aesthetic trends in genre writing are constantly evolving--and tense and point of view are no exception. The Princess Bride uses an omniscient viewpoint to excellent comedic effect, framing it inside a conversational first-person narrative. In the time since it was published, present-tense narration has grown in popularity, especially in Young Adult fiction. Where are fashions heading around tense and point of view? Which works are showcasing what the common viewpoints and tenses can contribute to a story?","loc":["Southfield"],"people":[{"name":"Jordan Kurella","id":"71"},{"name":"Dyrk Ashton","id":"45"},{"name":"Jason Sanford","id":"55"},{"name":"Amy Sundberg","id":"6"}]},{"id":"197","title":"Never go against a Sicilian when Beans are on the line","date":"2019-01-19","time":"11:00","mins":"60","desc":"Join us in the Teenfusion room for an intense game of Bean Boozled, where your sense of smell and tastebuds will be tested.","loc":["TeenFusion"]},{"id":"198","title":"Microeconomics in Fantasy Worlds","date":"2019-01-19","time":"12:00","mins":"60","desc":"In The Princess Bride, Vizzini reminds Fezzik he'd found him \"Unemployed in Greenland,â€ but details like rent and employment frequently go untouched in Fantasy Worldbuilding. Whether a setting uses coins or barter, there is still a need for characters to put food on the table, and making a living is a prime source of stress and conflict. How have budget and cashflow been examined in fantasy settings before, and what do they allow us to explore in new works?","loc":["Allen Park"],"people":[{"name":"Dan Stout","id":"34"},{"name":"Cassandra Morgan","id":"22"},{"name":"Stacey Filak","id":"121"},{"name":"K.A. Doore","id":"76"}]},{"id":"199","title":"Paint and Take (4hrs)","date":"2019-01-19","time":"12:00","mins":"60","loc":["Atrium"]},{"id":"200","title":"State of the Solar System","date":"2019-01-19","time":"12:00","mins":"60","desc":"What are humans and their robot pals doing out in the solar system right now? Where are we going and what's in the planning phases?","loc":["Erie"],"people":[{"name":"Martin L. Shoemaker","id":"91"},{"name":"Dr. Jennifer Piatek","id":"43"},{"name":"Bob Trembly","id":"16"}]},{"id":"201","title":"Workshop: Barbershipping","date":"2019-01-19","time":"12:00","mins":"60","desc":"If folk = filk, then barbershop = barbership. Learn to sing a song by the first filk barbershop quartet- Barbership!","loc":["Fairlane"]},{"id":"202","title":"Karuba","date":"2019-01-19","time":"12:00","mins":"60","desc":"Guide your adventurers skillfully through the jungle! All players choose to cards to play, lowest sum loses one. Use your cards to make a path to treasure, and safely to the temple.","loc":["Greenfield"]},{"id":"203","title":"AFTERNOON BREAK","date":"2019-01-19","time":"12:00","mins":"60","desc":"KidFusion is closed for one hour in the afternoon.","loc":["KidFusion"]},{"id":"204","title":"No Shrinking Violets: The Women of Genre Media","date":"2019-01-19","time":"12:00","mins":"60","desc":"From Dale Arden to Lois Lane to Emma Peel to Peggy Carter, genre women have been kicking ass and taking names since the very beginning.","loc":["Ontario"],"people":[{"name":"DI","id":"31"},{"name":"Bonnie Jones","id":"17"},{"name":"Jennifer Skwarski","id":"61"}]},{"id":"205","title":"Reading: Cat Rambo, Lawrence M. Schoen, Jeffrey Chapman","date":"2019-01-19","time":"12:00","mins":"60","loc":["Rotunda"],"people":[{"name":"Cat Rambo","id":"23"},{"name":"Jeffrey Chapman","id":"57"}]},{"id":"206","title":"TeenFusion Closes","date":"2019-01-19","time":"12:00","mins":"60","loc":["TeenFusion"]},{"id":"207","title":"Evolution of Fandom","date":"2019-01-19","time":"13:00","mins":"60","desc":"The only thing that stays the same in fandom is that it continues to change! How has it changed for the better, and how do we think it will continue to change?","loc":["Allen Park"],"people":[{"name":"Brian Bay","id":"19"},{"name":"Cat Rambo","id":"23"},{"name":"Julie Winningham","id":"74"},{"name":"Patrick Nielsen Hayden","id":"108"}]},{"id":"208","title":"The Nature of Time","date":"2019-01-19","time":"13:00","mins":"60","desc":"SF writers from H.G. Wells to Ted Chiang have obsessed over the nature of time. But what does the science say? Time travel, messages from the future, predestination: is any of this really possible? We will explore the ways new developments in science are threatening to upend our concept of time--and the ways that they already have.","loc":["Erie"],"people":[{"name":"David John Baker","id":"38"},{"name":"Mackenzie Flohr","id":"87"},{"name":"Derek Kunsken","id":"41"}]},{"id":"209","title":"Wizard","date":"2019-01-19","time":"13:00","mins":"60","desc":"trick-taking game based on Oh Hell. Assess your hand and your opponents to bid wisely. Play carefully to make your bid exactly, no more no less.","loc":["Greenfield"]},{"id":"210","title":"Simple Science","date":"2019-01-19","time":"13:00","mins":"60","desc":"Explore chemical reactions by making bouncy balls to take home.","loc":["KidFusion"]},{"id":"211","title":"Whose Cartoon Is It, Anyway?","date":"2019-01-19","time":"13:00","mins":"60","desc":"Whose Cartoon is It Anyway? The audience picks a cartoon plot, and artists jam to figure out what happens next! MC and Fan GoH Dave Stein narrates the story so that it makes sense. Or at least cartoon-sense.","loc":["Ontario"],"people":[{"name":"DI (M)","id":"32"},{"name":"Sean Martin","id":"120"},{"name":"BluRaven C. Houvener","id":"15"},{"name":"Emily Zelasko","id":"48"}]},{"id":"212","title":"Reading: Nino Cipri, Stacey Filak","date":"2019-01-19","time":"13:00","mins":"60","loc":["Rotunda"],"people":[{"name":"Nino Cipri","id":"106"}]},{"id":"213","title":"Supply Lines and Economics in Fantasy Worldbuilding","date":"2019-01-19","time":"13:00","mins":"60","desc":"Goldman's beloved abridged version of The Princess Bride omits the incisive political and economic commentary of Morganstern's classic, but understanding some basics about economics and trade is vital to fantasy world-building. What foods and fibers does your local ecology support? What trade routes are your characters connected to, and how long have they been established? We'll talk about how these things will influence a society's diet, architecture, clothing, and technology, as well as informing their class markers and aesthetics.","loc":["Southfield"],"people":[{"name":"Ferrett Steinmetz","id":"52"},{"name":"Jennifer Mace","id":"60"},{"name":"Scott H. Andrews","id":"119"},{"name":"Jon Skovron","id":"70"},{"name":"Teresa Nielsen Hayden","id":"126"}]},{"id":"214","title":"Kindness in Science Fiction and Fantasy","date":"2019-01-19","time":"14:00","mins":"60","desc":"How do we showcase characters' kindness in a world (or worlds) that can be cruel? Who does a good job of showing these interactions in their books (or other media!), and what makes their depictions feel real, nuanced, and effective? What about paradoxically kind books: stories focused on this type of interaction and also war, gore, and other serious interpersonal problems? How do they maintain both tone and values? What do we most need about stories of kindness right now, and how can they be dramatically effective?","loc":["Allen Park"],"people":[{"name":"Petra Kuppers","id":"111"},{"name":"Jennie Ivins","id":"59"},{"name":"Nibedita Sen","id":"105"}]},{"id":"215","title":"Women Over Fifty as Leaders, Mentors, and Heroes in SFF","date":"2019-01-19","time":"14:00","mins":"60","desc":"Robin Wright's transition from The Princess Bride's Buttercup to Wonder Woman's Antiope is emblematic of a larger trend in science fiction and fantasy: our princesses are becoming generals. Star Wars's General Organa, The Expanse's Chrisjen Avasarala, Legend of Korra's Lin Beifong, and The Broken Earth Trilogy's Essun--women's roles in genre fiction are expanding, and women whose comings of age are far behind them are refusing to be crowded off of the trails they blazed. Who are our favorite women over fifty in genre fiction? What roles would we like to see older women occupying more in our stories?","loc":["Dearborn"],"people":[{"name":"Suzanne Church","id":"124"},{"name":"Jeannie Szarama","id":"56"},{"name":"Sarah E. Gibbons","id":"117"},{"name":"Teresa Nielsen Hayden","id":"126"}]},{"id":"216","title":"Sorting Hat Chats","date":"2019-01-19","time":"14:00","mins":"60","desc":"By virtue of magic, the Sorting Hat is of course superior to all other methods of analyzing personality and potential, but beyond that pedigree, what recommends it to real world personality analysis? What can we learn about ourselves and others through an understanding of one's Hogwarts house?","loc":["Erie"],"people":[{"name":"Mackenzie Flohr","id":"87"}]},{"id":"217","title":"Master Labyrinth","date":"2019-01-19","time":"14:00","mins":"60","desc":"Players are charged with exploring the maze to find spell ingredients (numbered chips) to complete their journeyman project and become a Wizard. Chips must be claimed in order, and the maze constantly shifts for extra challenge.","loc":["Greenfield"]},{"id":"218","title":"Come Play With Me!","date":"2019-01-19","time":"14:00","mins":"60","desc":"Let's wind down with a selection of thinking and story-telling games.","loc":["KidFusion"]},{"id":"219","title":"Expanding The Definition of Witchcraft","date":"2019-01-19","time":"14:00","mins":"60","desc":"Witchcraft in fiction often taps into real world tragedies, myths and folklore, spiritual practices, sexuality and gender treatment through the lens of Western occultism. Witchcraft, however, is more than riding brooms or dancing naked. Panelists will explore the definition of witch and then provide examples of witches through underrepresented lenses.","loc":["Southfield"],"people":[{"name":"Josef Matulich","id":"72"},{"name":"Paul Kemner","id":"110"},{"name":"A. Carina Spears","id":"1"}]},{"id":"220","title":"KidFusion Closes","date":"2019-01-19","time":"15:00","mins":"60","desc":"Thanks for another great KidFusion year!","loc":["KidFusion"]},{"id":"221","title":"Closing Ceremonies","date":"2019-01-19","time":"15:00","mins":"60","desc":"Come say goodbye to our Guests of Honor and Special Guests, and learn what we might have in store for you for next year!","loc":["Michigan"],"people":[{"name":"Joe R. Lansdale","id":"64"},{"name":"Lewis Shiner","id":"85"},{"name":"Steve Macdonald","id":"123"},{"name":"Dr. Jennifer Piatek","id":"43"},{"name":"David M Stein","id":"39"},{"name":"DI","id":"31"},{"name":"Amy Sexsmith","id":"5"}]},{"id":"222","title":"Feedback Session","date":"2019-01-19","time":"16:00","mins":"60","desc":"Give the ConCom compliments, ask questions, provide concerns. Review the con experience with the all-volunteer concom and staff, and find out how to join in the fun of planning ConFusion for next year!","loc":["Michigan"]}];